===Etymology 1===
Old English [[Leodis]] (a Celtic kingdom), from a Brythonic Celtic term indicating ‘people living by the fast-flowing river’.

====Proper noun====
'''Leeds'''
# A [[city]] in [[West Yorkshire]], [[England]]

===Etymology 2===
Old English [[Hledes]], probably from a stream-name.

====Proper noun====
'''Leeds'''
# A [[village]] in [[Kent]], the site of [[w:Leeds Castle|Leeds Castle]]

